In Need for Speed: The Run is competing all over America.
Review
A journey, in principle careless, is complicated by a series of improper carelessness of a routine journey during tomorrow's shift.
To some extent, expectations were met, but this is of no use, if, in fact, nothing extraordinary was meant to be done.
The new delivery, to which the title is added The Run, raised great expectations already before its premiere.
He promised that he would give new air to the old "Need for Speed" race saga and, as a result of what was shown, appears as a game that should not end up again being a genre of action without more.
We also feel curious to know how the scenes would be inserted, where the main character descends from the car and walks by his own foot.
As is often the case in the NFS series, the results do not vary much from what we expected.
There are races that can be considered acceptable, but in the total computation points are lost because of absurd failures, which have already appeared in the series for years.
In fact, we cannot even call mistakes, but rather the incomprehensible misgivings of programmers.
The adventure starts very well.
You are introduced into a story, whose protagonist, Jack, has certain personal problems; to solve them, you are offered to participate in an illegal career all over America.
You sit at the wheel on the west coast, in San Francisco, and your mission is to get the first to New York.
The idea is to offer something interesting.
The route is divided into ten stages and then into more than fifty races.
It follows that each race takes place on a different route and the stages are located in different environments, which are quite diverse and interesting.
In this way, one does not even remotely have the feeling that the game always offers the same.
Some of the environments are even pleasant to see, although the technical level of the graph is equivalent to that of previous series deliveries.
So, it's nothing from the other world.
But the desert walk, the autumn landscape or the high snow-covered mountains produce a very pleasant visual effect.
In addition, the races are diversified from time to time by an atypical element.
So, for example, in the desert you find yourself a sandstorm that reduces visibility.
In the mountains, however, you must be careful not to be buried in an avalanche.
According to that, each race is very well developed.
There's only a couple of models, but that's enough.
For a moment, you try to advance a number of required rivals (the normal in a classic race), then you try to earn time (classic timed duel) and then you are expected to have a duel against a single adversary.
In the midst of all this the police sometimes appear, which only makes things more difficult.
The novelty is the landscapes outside the car.
Interactive animations are presented when Jack, in most cases, has to escape someone and you have to help him, always by pressing the button right at the right time.
Nothing complicated.
It is surprising, however, that there are far less landscapes in the game than one could expect (in particular there are only three).
But the final result is positive, because this element does not become annoying and, in the context already mentioned, it is one of the elements that make the game more interesting.
The driving model follows the traces of the previous episodes.
That means that today is no longer a big deal, but it cannot be said to be bad.
If you look for a realistic simulation, you can look elsewhere.
But a career conceived with a lot of action is well suited to this style of driving, although we can find something better among the games of the competition.
So far, all in order.
But the problems arise after a certain time.
Unlike the correct driving models, the same is no longer true for collisions.
From games of this type you cannot expect to recreate complicated deformations and collisions, but in fact before a hit against any object, you cannot predict how your car will react, which is not all in order.
It is typical that, by making a very tight advance or circulating the car with a normal traffic, there are only light oaks, but in other almost identical situations, your car ends up making out of control.
Or it even ends up totally destroyed.
Thanks to the reset system, there are no big problems, but it can put you in a bad mood.
The resets are programmed in such a way that, when you suffer an accident or get off the track, the game will return you to the last rescue point on the track.
However, in each race, only five resets are available.
If you consume all of them, you have to restart the race from the beginning.
So it's just a help in case something doesn't go right, but it's not very reliable.
Sometimes, not even the reset helps, it only helps to learn the given stage of memory.
A great disadvantage of the game is that the same facts are repeated in different places.
In some curves, for example, you have to enter in a specific way; otherwise, they are impossible to take.
Other times you find yourself in some place "civilian" vehicles always with the same configuration, even if you are the first, fifth or arrive five minutes before or after.
This makes the most of all rabies in situations, when you see that two cars that go to meet in opposite directions, your opponent goes forward without problems, but when you arrive, you must either turn or stop.
It's the same when you get there, because it's programmed because the "surprise" will always happen in front of your nose.
The adversaries also have one more advantage.
Throughout the game you will reach places where, without taking into account the moment, the same adversary will always advance you in the same place.
This also happens at the end of the game, on a long bridge, which is even more shocking.
Your opponent must come before you, at any price.
When he goes in front of you, it makes it difficult for you to see the cars that come from front, so at first you can make the car paddle.
You can understand the idea of creating a game with maximum doses of suspense and adrenaline, but the execution is so apparent that it will probably disappoint you right away.
And it's a shame, because even if the travel model is simple, the game is fun and with action, so it's often not possible to follow the detail what happens or where.
And it really doesn't matter, if merit takes the idea with fifty exclusive tracks or classification in the race so that it doesn't fit boredom, or anything else.
An unusual idea is the change of cars during the races.
You have to be attentive to the gas dispensers next to the road, because right there you have to change your car, although in the vast majority of cases you will have enough of what you have.
The cars are divided into three categories.
Sports are suitable for urban areas, strong American cars for straight highways and super-sports exotic cars for technical driving, for example, on mountain roads with curves.
In addition, the main narrative thread also appears a parallel thread of challenges, that is, there are races in specific places that you will know for the stories.
Here you will get not only medals, but also points of experience for your profile, which serves both challenges and stories.
By reaching the top level, the driver opens up several possibilities, starting with the car and ending with funds for the profile.
At the same time, there is an Autolog online function that compares your results with those of other players and provides other community functions.
One of the most difficult elements to understand is how the last race in history is made.
With the car you reach the subway tunnel (pass), where you run in the dark on the tracks (pass).
The speedometer marks you between 150 and 200 km / h (pass) and, suddenly, behind you comes the subway convoy and you are just taken ahead.
In the writing we will surely have a discussion about this for several days, about whether during the game's programming none even thought a little or whether the real authors take us for a bunch of bobbles.
The technical part of the game is nothing extraordinary, but at least the general visual effects result in most cases pleasant, sometimes even superb.
What a shame that, at the most tense times, the quality of the image is reduced and, at times, in a serious way.
This mainly affects accidents involving many participants, when the continuous image quality is no longer valid.
The audio is fine and the soundtrack is a matter of taste.
In order to please most of the youth group, the soundtrack belongs to the category "each of their father and mother," but it can be assumed that no one would buy the game just for their music.
The final feeling of Need for Speed: The Run is therefore quite confusing.
If the game avoided absolutely silly mistakes, we would have trouble saying that The Run is the best NFS game of recent years.
It gives the feeling that the game is not over.
The fun is assured, but get ready because the mistakes will hit you in the eyes with the strength of some airport reflectors.
The chorus of the Carolina University will participate in the concert "Students of Terciopolo."
The joint celebration of International Student Day and the anniversary of the Terciopolo Revolution as a musical experience will take place for the third time at the Festa Acadérica festival.
Twenty corals of high school and university centres will be presented during this session.
The festival revolves around two concerts on November 17.
"Carolina University has a high participation in the festival."
Among the current chorus are the coral of the Faculty of Pedagogy and the Faculty of Humanities, in the committee of the festival is rector Václav Hampl, "said the organization's head, Jakub Čaloun.
The summit of the entire festival is the free entrance for all audiences to the high school chorus concert, which will be held on March 17 at 14 hours in front of the National Technical Library in Dejvice.
The program is attended by Czech jazzist Karel Růžička and his Jazz Mass Celebration.
In the evening, the "Students of Terciopolo" concert will be held at the Municipal House's celebration places in Vynohrady, where university corals, including the Uninversity Carolina chorus, will participate.
The purpose of the Academic Festa is not only to celebrate the International Students' Day and to remember the twenty-second anniversary of the Terciopolo Revolution, but also to present to the public coral music at the highest level and to promote collaborative creation among young people.
The main organizer is the Czech Coral Union in collaboration with the Jan Kepler High School.
All the events were supported by the mayor of Prague, Bohuslav Svoboda, and the rector of Carolina University, Václav Hampl.
The Festival will take place between November 16 and 20 between Prague and Pardubice.
The calendar offers, in addition to the concerts, a whole series of musical events, improvised student shows and morning concerts.
More information can be found at the festival page www.festaacademica.cz
