Mujica travels to Mexico to strengthen political ties
An official conference, led by Uruguayan President José Mujica, and composed of several ministers and entrepreneurs, will begin on Tuesday a visit to Mexico in order to expand trade between the two nations and address political issues in the region.
Mujica will meet next Wednesday with her Mexican partner, Felipe Calderón, the highest point of an extensive agenda of meetings with political, commercial authorities and a meeting with the Uruguayan community resident in Mexico, according to the agenda spread by the Uruguayan Presidency.
The meeting between the two presidents, in the city of Guadalajara, will "be conducive to the exchange of information in all that is the political affairs between the two nations," according to the South American presidency on its website.
According to local media, Mujica would seek to get Calderón to support Uruguay in the incident with France when the French president, Nicolas Sarkozy, included the South American country on a list of tax havens, at the G20 meeting in the French city of Cannes.
In his speech, Sarkozy threatened to exclude from the international community those countries that remain tax havens, a statement that led to Uruguay's rejection and the call to consult its ambassador in the European country.
Mexico has since November chaired the G20, a group of the most powerful emerging and developed countries in the world, and has been in force with the South American country, since January this year, an agreement to exchange tax information in order to avoid double taxation.
The Uruguayan government has tried in recent years to speed up the implementation of tax exchange agreements in order to get out of the "grey list" of the Organization for Economic Cooperation and Development (OECD), made up of countries that did not implement all international standards of tax cooperation.
At the commercial level, Mexico and Uruguay have had a Free Trade Agreement (FTA) since 2004, which has increased the exchange of goods between the two nations.
The bigotudo plumber passes the three dimensions with "Super Mario 3D Land"
Super Mario has fought, tirelessly, over 25 years to save Princess Peach from the claws of the evil Bowser, but he has never done so in three dimensions to date: in "Super Mario 3D Land" he will fight for the love of the girl in stereoscopic technology.
The title, which comes this month to shops all over the world, has been designed from the beginning to take advantage of the features of the Nintendo 3DS portable console, which allows you to play in three dimensions without wearing glasses.
"Mario is the character who has to say how stereoscopy without glasses should work," said Nintendo's specialist press officer in Spain, Omar Alvarez, during the presentation of the video game in Madrid.
Alvarez indicated that "Super Mario 3D Land" is "Nintendo's first video game originally thought for that support," since so far successes such as "Star Fox 64 3D" or "Zelda: Ocarine of time 3D" were adaptations to existing titles.
Nintendo's spokesman has argued that, despite being 3D, "Super Mario 3D Land" is a "accessible" video game that allows you to enjoy a quick and smooth game.
Alvarez has stated that "Super Mario 3D Land" contains two games in one: the first part is "simple" to hook up the less skilled users.
Once overcome, the most experienced will be able to give a "second round" to the levels of play, which this time present greater difficulty.
In addition, users will be able to choose in real time between an "aggressive D" or one that only affects the depth of the action, but it will be necessary to play in three dimensions in order to overcome the different challenges and "not succumb to optical illusions."
This incursion of Super Mario in the three dimensions also involves the return of the character to a portable console, a fact that has not occurred since 2005.
In this video game Nintendo winks at the followers of the saga and repeats the formula of the success of the previous deliveries, which is that the moustache plumber will have to go through dangerous mined platforms with the aim of releasing Princess Peach.
Although the player will find new in the movements, environments, costumes and enemies and also a "playable" Luigi.
